    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIn https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34770#issuecomment-3042463911 I proposed a method to hook into `vim.pack.add`, mainly to run some code after adding the packages. Problem with the \"wrapped\" solution is that the user has to do some spec resolving themself. It would be easier if `vim.pack.add()` returns the resolved spec of the just-added packages.\n\nBonus if the resolved version and the path are also returned (similar to PackChanged events).\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAbility to do this:\n\n```lua\nlocal specs = vim.pack.add({ ... })\nfor _, spec in ipairs(specs) do\n  pcall(require, 'plugins.' .. spec.name)\nend\n```\n\n```lua\nlocal plugs = vim.pack.add({ ... })\nfor _, plug in ipairs(plugs) do\n  -- just a dumb example to showcase use of plug.path\n  local size = vim.split(vim.system({'du', '-sh', plug.path }):wait().stdout, '\\t')[1]\n  vim.print(('loaded plugin %s (%s)'):format(plug.spec.name, size))\nend\n```",
